verbose_text: The Hydrologic and Water Quality System (HAWQS1.0) (https://epahawqs.tamu.edu/, last access : 15 November 2018) was recently developed by the USEPA Office of Water to enhance the usability of SWAT in simulating effects of land management practices based on an extensive array of crops, soils, natural vegetation types, land uses, and climate change scenarios on hydrology and water quality.
